@startuml IDEATION_JOURNEY
title 
Pre-Development Ideation (Human -> Artifact -> Agent Pipeline)
Translating Abstract Vision into Concrete Architecture & Initialization
end title

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333333
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF3CD
skinparam NoteBorderColor #333333

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor<<HUMAN>> #C8E6C9
  BackgroundColor<<AGENT>> #F8D7DA
  BackgroundColor<<FILE>> #E3F2FD
}

|#C8E6C9|Human| Human Ideator
|#E3F2FD|Artifacts| Generated Documents
|#F8D7DA|Agent| Coding Agent (Process Steward)

|Human|
start
:1. Define Application Purpose & Value
----
**What:** The genesis of the project begins with
defining the exact problem you intend to solve.
Before mapping out any engineering topologies,
you must conduct a SWOT analysis alongside a
Lean Canvas to establish a definitive Value
Proposition that dictates market necessity.

**How:** Execute Jobs-to-be-Done (JTBD) theory
to map out primary User Personas, establishing
their unique pain points. Outline macro-level
User Journeys required to satisfy behaviors
using a strict Value Proposition Canvas (VPC).

**With What:** Deploy the following structural pairs:

1. [Miro] + [BPMN 2.0] -> Produces the macro
   `business_process_web.bpmn` workflow artifact.
2. [FigJam] + [Lean Canvas] -> Produces formal
   `lean_canvas.md` market value tracker metrics.
3. [Obsidian] + [UML / TOGAF] -> Produces the
   `use_case_model.uml` linking actors to limits.
4. [Claude/GPT4] -> Acts strictly as an external
   adversarial bouncing board for market critique.;
|Artifacts|
:<b><color:#1565C0>Product Ideation Canvas</color></b>
(Miro / Obsidian)
====
**<color:#2e7d32>[Strictly Human Output]</color>**
• `lean_canvas.md`
• `business_process_web.bpmn`
• `use_case_model.uml`
• `jobs_to_be_done_matrix.doc`
• `value_proposition_canvas.pdf`;

|Human|
:2. Define Architectural Constraints
----
**What:** With physical business logic defined,
you must immediately translate abstract needs
into a hard, unforgiving engineering topology
strictly adhering to 12-Factor App methodology.

**How:** Declare exact Frontend and Backend
stacks required. Decide if the product demands
heavy SSR capabilities (Next.js) or backend
throughput (FastAPI). Evaluate CAP Theorem limits
(Consistency vs Availability) to safely lock in
schemas (PostgreSQL vs MongoDB). Finally, map 
Cloud deployment topologies alongside extreme
Threat Modeling (STRIDE framework limits) and
AES-256 encryption laws via C4 modeling rules.

**With What:** Map strict limits by utilizing:

1. [Draw.io] + [UML / C4] -> Produces both the
   `component_architecture.uml` mapping modules,
   and `C4_context_diagram.drawio` visual layers.
2. [Excalidraw] + [UML] -> Produces the literal
   `deployment_topology.uml` showing Cloud VPCs.
3. [Notion] + [STRIDE] -> Produces the formal
   `stride_threat_model.md` defining secure limits.
4. [Agent Engine] -> `/plan` formally delegates
   the raw `database_schema.sql` generation layer.;
|Artifacts|
:<b><color:#1565C0>Engineering Topology</color></b>
(Draw.io / Excalidraw)
====
**<color:#2e7d32>[Strictly Human Output]</color>**
• `C4_context_diagram.drawio`
• `component_architecture.uml`
• `deployment_topology.uml`
• `stride_threat_model.md`

**<color:#c62828>[Delegatable to Agent]</color>**
• `database_schema.sql`
• `api_endpoints.json`;

|Human|
:3. Map Agile Scrum Hierarchy
----
**What:** Because unstructured abstract goals are
impossible for agents to execute, you fracture
the massive architectural blueprint into tightly
bound, modular development clusters via Scrum.

**How:** Run aggressive Event Storming sessions
to execute Domain-Driven Design (DDD), isolating
bounded capabilities—like severing Auth from
Billing. These domains translate into Business
Epics. Deploy User Story Mapping to explicitly
slice Epics down into granular logic stories.
Note: You can enforce Behavior-Driven Dev (BDD)
rules via Gherkin Syntax for acceptance criteria.

**With What:** Execute data conversion bridging via:

1. [Miro] + [Event Storming] -> Slices Epics into
   `event_storming_epics.jira` tracker payloads.
2. [Whimsical] + [UML Seq] -> Translates backend
   routing into precise `api_sequence.uml` routes.
3. [Whimsical] + [UML Act] -> Maps UX workflows
   natively producing `ux_activity_flow.uml`.
4. [Figma] + [Wardley Mapping] -> Produces literal
   strategic `ui_wireframes.fig` mockups.
5. [Linear] + [BDD/Gherkin] -> Translates payload
   into `bdd_gherkin_acceptance_criteria.md`.;
|Artifacts|
:<b><color:#1565C0>Agile Scrum Environment</color></b>
(Jira / Figma / Whimsical)
====
**<color:#2e7d32>[Strictly Human Output]</color>**
• `event_storming_epics.jira`
• `ui_wireframes.fig`
• `api_sequence.uml`
• `ux_activity_flow.uml`

**<color:#c62828>[Delegatable to Agent]</color>**
• `user_stories.linear`
• `bdd_gherkin_acceptance_criteria.md`;

|Human|
:4. The Translation Funnel (Pre-Flight)
----
**What:** LLM agents operate against finite context
windows. You cannot dump thirty pages of C4
diagrams and unstructured Figma wireframes
without crashing the AI execution pipeline.

**How:** Act as a strict data compression funnel.
Employ the MoSCoW Method (Must-Haves vs Won't
Haves) to vigorously distill sprawling Phase 1
through 3 data into a concentrated syntax string.
Prune away non-essential UI opinions, forcing your
payload to focus strictly on structural OpenAPI
routing conventions, schema hooks, and core logic.

**With What:** Employ the extraction loop via:

1. [VSCode Editor] + [MoSCoW] -> Physically 
   ingests the distilled UML and BPMN metrics, 
   typing them exclusively into the localized 
   `# Vision` constraint boundary mapped natively 
   inside the `product/PRD.md` repository artifact.;
|Artifacts|
:<b><color:#1565C0>product/PRD.md</color></b>
(Human distills the precise MoSCoW method
variables exclusively into the `# Vision` string);

|Human|
:5. Native System Validation;
|Agent|
:Execute **<color:#2e7d32>/seed</color>** subroutine
----
Validates CI loops, physical directories,
and verifies automated compilation engines.;

|Human|
:6. Trigger System Initialization;
|Agent|
:Execute **<color:#2e7d32>/plan</color>** subroutine
----
The Agent autonomously ingests and parses
the exact `# Vision` string limits.;
:System Drafts Execution Parameters
----
Agent mathematically extracts architectures.;
|Artifacts|
:<b><color:#1565C0>product/PRD.md</color></b>
**<color:#c62828>[Agent-Generated Target]</color>**
(Agent writes Story S-### arrays natively);

:<b><color:#1565C0>product/ARCH.md</color></b>
**<color:#c62828>[Agent-Generated Target]</color>**
(Agent drafts master tech rule limits & SQL);

:<b><color:#1565C0>product/contracts/*</color></b>
**<color:#c62828>[Agent-Generated Target]</color>**
(Agent maps literal API data boundaries);

|Human|
:7. Phase A System Review
----
Human rigorously audits cross-layer outputs.;
|Artifacts|
:<b><color:#1565C0>Review Architecture Output</color></b>
(Must visually compare PRD against ARCH);
|Human|
if (Are constraints valid?) then (no/hallucination)
  :Run **/advise** & **/explore**
  ----
  Force Agent to test edge cases logically.;
  |Agent|
  :Run Sandbox Engine Loop
  ----
  Validate architecture internally and explicitly
  write a `D-###` decision ratification log.;
else (yes/approved)
  |Human|
  :Human Authorizes Plan
  ----
  Explicitly typing 'Approved' locks rules.;
endif

|Agent|
:Architecture Physically Locked
----
Agent initialized securely. It is now primed
to begin Phase B execution loops (**/next**).;
stop

@enduml
